When a new person joins a company, the overview session you give them is commonly called Induction or Onboarding.
What it is called
Induction Program (very common in India)
Employee Onboarding
New Joiner Orientation
Company Orientation
ğŸ”¹ Induction usually refers to the first-day or first-week overview
ğŸ”¹ Onboarding is broader and may span weeks or months
What should be covered in an Induction / Onboarding Overview
1. Company Introduction
Company name, history & vision
Mission & core values
Products / services
Key clients or markets
2. Organization Structure
Founders / leadership team
Departments & their roles
Reporting hierarchy
Where the new employee fits in
3. Role-Specific Overview
Job responsibilities
Expectations & KPIs
Immediate goals (first 30â€“60â€“90 days)
Tools/software they will use
4. HR & Policy Overview
Working hours & attendance
Leave policy & holidays
Code of conduct
Payroll, salary cycle, benefits
IT & security policies
5. Workplace & Culture
Company culture & work ethics
Communication norms
Dress code (if any)
Remote / hybrid rules
6. Tools & Access
Email & internal tools
Project management tools
Communication tools (Slack, Teams, etc.)
Documentation/wiki access
7. Compliance & Formalities
NDA / employment agreement
ID cards
System access
Any mandatory training
8. Introduction to Team
Team members
Buddy/mentor assignment
Whom to contact for what
